                  </hi>. I am a merchant's clerk, and live with my father at Bermondsey—on 28th June, a little before 9 in the evening, I was passing over London-bridge—a horse fell down, which caused a crowd to assemble—I waited a moment there, and felt a tug at my watch-guard—I looked round and saw my watch in the prisoner's hand—I have not seen it since—my chain was not broken—I caught hold of him, he pushed his hands into the crowd, and then said, "Search me"—I had a friend there—I caught him and gave him in custody.</p>
